"title": "5845: emptiness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5845",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture stresses the emptiness of human life without God, and notes that Jesus Christ chose to empty himself in order to redeem humanity.</p>\n<h2>Emptiness and creation</h2>\n<h3>The world created to be filled</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:18\">ISA 45:18</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:14\">HAB 2:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:2\">GEN 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>Emptiness as a symbol of judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:23\">JER 4:23</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Human life can be empty</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:21\">RUT 1:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl1:2\">ECC 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl3:19\">ECC 3:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl12:8\">ECC 12:8</a></p>\n<h2>Human words can be empty</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job35:13\">JOB 35:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job35:16\">JOB 35:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:6\">ISA 16:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:5\">ISA 36:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:20\">2KI 18:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:4\">ISA 59:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:6\">EPH 5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:18\">2PE 2:18</a></p>\n<h2>Human attempts at fulfilment are empty</h2>\n<h3>Work does not satisfy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:2\">ISA 55:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps127:1-Ps127:2\">PSA 127:1–127:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:17\">ECC 2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl6:7\">ECC 6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:5-Hag1:6\">HAG 1:5–1:6</a></p>\n<h3>Pleasure does not last</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job20:5\">JOB 20:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:17\">PRO 21:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:1-Eccl2:3\">ECC 2:1–2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:25\">ECC 2:25</a></p>\n<h3>Wealth does not satisfy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:10\">ECC 5:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:7-Eccl4:8\">ECC 4:7–4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:15\">LUK 12:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:9-1Tim6:10\">1TI 6:9–6:10</a></p>\n<h3>Material possessions are unreliable</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:18-Luke12:20\">LUK 12:18–12:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job8:13-Job8:15\">JOB 8:13–8:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:31\">JOB 15:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:10\">PSA 49:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:12\">PSA 49:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:16-Ps49:17\">PSA 49:16–49:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:4\">PRO 11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:15\">ECC 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:7\">1TI 6:7</a></p>\n<h3>False religion cannot save</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:13\">ISA 57:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg10:14\">JDG 10:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:17-Isa44:18\">ISA 44:17–44:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:20\">ISA 45:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:7\">ISA 46:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:12\">JER 11:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:15\">ACT 14:15</a></p>\n<h2>Emptiness as the result of sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:13-Mic6:14\">MIC 6:13–6:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:14-Lev26:16\">LEV 26:14–26:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:32-Ps78:33\">PSA 78:32–78:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:10\">HOS 4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:7-Hag1:9\">HAG 1:7–1:9</a></p>\n<h2>God wants to remove the emptiness of people's lives</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:18\">1PE 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps81:10\">PSA 81:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:16\">JHN 1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:10\">JHN 10:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:13\">EPH 4:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:10\">COL 2:10</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ accepts emptiness in order to redeem humanity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:7\">PHP 2:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:9\">2CO 8:9</a></p>",
